87void StructParametersParser::Parse(absl::string_view src) {
88 size_t i = 0;
89 while (i < src.length()) {
90 size_t val_end = FindOrEnd(src, i, ',');
91 size_t colon_pos = FindOrEnd(src, i, ':');
92 size_t key_end = std::min(val_end, colon_pos);
93 size_t val_begin = key_end + 1u;
94 absl::string_view key(src.substr(i, key_end - i));
95 absl::string_view opt_value;
96 if (val_end >= val_begin)
97 opt_value = src.substr(val_begin, val_end - val_begin);
98 i = val_end + 1u;
99 bool found = false;
100 for (auto& member : members_) {
101 if (key == member.key) {
102 found = true;
103 if (!member.parser.parse(opt_value, member.member_ptr)) {
104 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Failed to read field with key: '" << key
105 << "' in trial: \"" << src << "\"";
106 }
107 break;
108 }
109 }
110 // "_" is be used to prefix keys that are part of the string for
111 // debugging purposes but not neccessarily used.
112 // e.g. WebRTC-Experiment/param: value, _DebuggingString
113 if (!found && (key.empty() || key[0] != '_')) {
114 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "No field with key: '" << key
115 << "' (found in trial: \"" << src << "\")";
116 }
117 }
118}

120std::string StructParametersParser::Encode() const {
121 std::string res;
122 bool first = true;
123 for (const auto& member : members_) {
124 if (!first)
125 res += ",";
126 res += member.key;
127 res += ":";
128 member.parser.encode(member.member_ptr, &res);
129 first = false;
130 }
131 return res;
